# Care Connect API Documentation — Modules 7 & 8

---

## Module 7: Property Filter API

All endpoints require authentication via `Authorization: Bearer <jwt_token>` header.  
Access: Any authenticated role (USER, ASSOCIATE, ADMIN).

---

### 7.1 Filter Properties

**Endpoint:** `GET /api/v1/properties`

**Headers:**

```
Authorization: Bearer <jwt_token>
```

**Query Parameters:**

| Parameter   | Type    | Required | Description                                               |
| ----------- | ------- | -------- | --------------------------------------------------------- |
| `type`      | string  | No       | Property type: `residential`, `commercial`, or `acres`    |
| `min_price` | integer | No       | Minimum price filter (inclusive)                           |
| `max_price` | integer | No       | Maximum price filter (inclusive)                           |
| `city`      | string  | No       | City name (partial match, case-insensitive)               |
| `page`      | integer | No       | Page number, 1-based (default: `1`)                       |
| `limit`     | integer | No       | Items per page (default: `10`, max: `50`)                 |

**Example Request:**

```
GET /api/v1/properties?type=residential&city=Mumbai&min_price=2000000&page=1&limit=10
```

**Success Response** `200 OK`:

```json
{
  "success": true,
  "message": "Properties fetched successfully",
  "data": {
    "properties": [
      {
        "id": "b3f2c5a1-7e4d-4a89-9c12-3d5e6f7a8b9c",
        "title": "Luxury 3BHK Apartment in Bandra West",
        "price": 8500000,
        "location": "Mumbai",
        "type": "flat",
        "created_at": "2026-02-15T10:30:00Z"
      },
      {
        "id": "a1d4e7b2-6c3f-4e91-8b0a-2c4d5e6f7a8b",
        "title": "Spacious 2BHK in Andheri East",
        "price": 4500000,
        "location": "Mumbai",
        "type": "flat",
        "created_at": "2026-01-20T14:45:00Z"
      }
    ],
    "total_count": 42,
    "current_page": 1,
    "total_pages": 5
  }
}
```

> **Type Mapping:** The `type` query parameter maps to internal values:  
> `residential` → `flat` | `commercial` → `commercial` | `acres` → `plot`

