## Module 8: Community APIs

All endpoints require authentication via `Authorization: Bearer <jwt_token>` header.  
Access: Any authenticated role (USER, ASSOCIATE, ADMIN).

---

### 8.1 Create Community

**Endpoint:** `POST /api/v1/communities`

**Headers:**

```
Authorization: Bearer <jwt_token>
Content-Type: application/json
```

**Request Body:**

```json
{
  "name": "Mumbai Property Owners",
  "description": "A community for property owners in Mumbai to share tips and market updates."
}
```

| Field         | Type   | Required | Description                    |
| ------------- | ------ | -------- | ------------------------------ |
| `name`        | string | Yes      | Name of the community          |
| `description` | string | No       | Description of the community   |

**Success Response** `201 Created`:

```json
{
  "success": true,
  "message": "Community created successfully",
  "data": {
    "id": "f7a8b9c0-1d2e-4f3a-b5c6-7d8e9f0a1b2c",
    "name": "Mumbai Property Owners",
    "description": "A community for property owners in Mumbai to share tips and market updates.",
    "created_by": "c4d5e6f7-8a9b-4c0d-1e2f-3a4b5c6d7e8f",
    "created_at": "2026-03-07T18:30:00Z"
  }
}
```

> **Note:** The creator is automatically added as a member of the community.

---

