## Standard Error Format

All endpoints follow the global error response structure:

```json
{
  "success": false,
  "message": "A human-readable description of the error",
  "error_code": "NOT_FOUND",
  "errors": null
}
```

| Error Code              | HTTP Status | Description                                    |
| ----------------------- | ----------- | ---------------------------------------------- |
| `BAD_REQUEST`           | 400         | Malformed request or invalid parameters        |
| `UNAUTHORIZED`          | 401         | Missing or invalid JWT token                   |
| `FORBIDDEN`             | 403         | Insufficient permissions for the resource      |
| `NOT_FOUND`             | 404         | Requested resource does not exist              |
| `CONFLICT`              | 409         | Duplicate resource conflict                    |
| `VALIDATION_ERROR`      | 422         | Request body validation failures               |
| `INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR` | 500         | Unexpected server-side error                   |

For validation errors, the `errors` field contains a map of field names to error message arrays:

```json
{
  "success": false,
  "message": "Validation failed",
  "error_code": "VALIDATION_ERROR",
  "errors": {
    "field_name": ["Error message 1", "Error message 2"]
  }
}
```
